TION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tamil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Eelam </ORGANIZATION> was involved in the killings,'' the statement said. An <ORGANIZATION> Indian </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> High </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> spokesman, who can not be identified under briefing rules, denied the mission had suggested a Tamil Tiger involvement. `` Perhaps it is only their guilty conscience speaking,'' he said, refusing to elaborate. Tamils comprise 18 percent of <LOCATION> Sri </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lanka </LOCATION>'s 16 million people. The rebels claim Tamils are discriminated against by the Sinhalese, who make up 75 percent of the population and control the government and the military. The <ORGANIZATION> Tamil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> United </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Liberation </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Front </ORGANIZATION> has differed with demands by the government and the Tiger rebels that Indian soldiers posted on the island nation be withdrawn. The demand followed talks in May between the rebels and the government, the first direct contact between the two sides since the <ORGANIZATION> Tamil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tigers </ORGANIZATION> launched a war for an independent nation in 1983. Amirthalingam in public statements welcomed the demand but said the withdrawal should be gradual and done only after political powers were given to the Tamils. <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> has said it will pull out its estimated 40,000 troops after this condition is met. <PERSON> Amirthalingam </PERSON>, a lawyer, was elected to <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION> in 1956. His party became the second largest group in <ORGANIZATION> Parliament </ORGANIZATION> after the 1977 elections but was relegated to the background after the <ORGANIZATION> Tamil </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Tigers </ORGANIZATION> launched their militant movement. <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> became involved in <LOCATIO