<HEAD>Two Revolutions Compared at Washington Festivities</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By GENE KRAMER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Hatred of tyranny inspired the revolutions that led to independence for the <LOCATION> United </LOCATION> <LOCATION> States </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>, retired <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Chief Justice <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> Burger </PERSON> said Friday. <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> and French officials gathered on the steps of the Jefferson Memorial to mark the 200th anniversary of the storming of the Bastille. Youngsters sang the `` La Marseillaise'' and `` The Star Spangled Banner,'' the <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Band </ORGANIZATION> played the French march `` Father of Victory,'' and senators joined in reading the French Declaration of the Rights of Man and of the Citizen and the <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Bill of Rights. French Ambassador <PERSON> Emmanuel </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Margerie </PERSON> said the ideas of <ORGANIZATION> Voltaire </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Rousseau </PERSON> and other French thinkers of the Age of Enlightenment inspired <PERSON> Thomas </PERSON> <PERSON> Jefferson </PERSON> as he wrote the Declaration of Independence. `` The winds from <LOCATION> America </LOCATION> blew over <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>'' with their message of liberty, democracy and human rights, he said. Iaugurating a postage stamp marking the French Revolution, <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> Postmaster General <PERSON> Anthony </PERSON> <PERSON> M. </PERSON> <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> said the fall of the Bastille was a triumph of `` patriots over tyrants who made peaceful revolution impossible.'' Burger, <PERSON> Frank </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> U.S. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Army </ORGANIZATION> Secretary <PERSON> John </PERSON> <PERSON> O. </PERSON> <PERSON> Marsh </PERSON> <PERSON> Jr. </PERSON> said the military contributions of the <PERSON> Marquis </PERSON> <PERSON> Gilbert </PERSON> <PERSON> de </PERSON> <PERSON> Lafayette </PERSON>, Admiral de <L