 the <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION>. His lawyer, <PERSON> Jonathan </PERSON> <PERSON> Kuttab </PERSON>, accused government interrogators of depriving <PERSON> Hamayel </PERSON> of food and sleep, forcing him to stand with a sack over his head, and handcuffing him in uncomfortable positions. `` I do n't know of any country in the world where a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> citizen can be held for so long and interrogated so roughly without any charges,'' <PERSON> Kuttab </PERSON> said.
