<HEAD>Rules Proposed for Security Ban on Foreign Takeovers</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By CARL HARTMAN</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>WASHINGTON (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Proposed rules that would allow President <PERSON> Bush </PERSON> to plead national security and block takeover of a <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> firm by foreigners were published for public comment Friday by the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION>. Sen. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> Exon </PERSON>, D-Neb., and Rep. <PERSON> James </PERSON> <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Florio </PERSON>, <LOCATION> D-N.J. </LOCATION>, who were responsible for parts of the law, praised the proposed regulations published in the Federal Register Comments may be submitted by Sept. 12, although the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> said later comments will be considered if possible. The Trade Act, signed by former President <PERSON> Reagan </PERSON> last August, provides authority for the rules that would allow the president to block a merger if he has credible evidence that the foreign interest taking control might act to hurt <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> security. If he decides on an investigation, he gets 30 days to begin it, 45 days to complete it and another 15 days to announce it. <PERSON> Florio </PERSON> said the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION> has interpreted the law broadly to make sure that it covers different ways that a foreign firm could take over an <LOCATION> American </LOCATION> one: a joint venture, buying up the assets, and defaults on loans as well as just buying a majority interest. `` In my view, all methods by which foreign control may be accomplished must be covered, including proxy solicitations which are certainly as viable a means of establishing control as equity ownership,'' he added in a statement. A proxy authorizes a person to cast the vote of stock owned by someone else. If an acquiring company gets enough proxies, it can take over a firm without paying a premium price for the stock. `` I am very pleased with action taken by the secretary of the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION>,'' <PERSON> Exon </PERSON> told the <ORGANIZATION> Assocated </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Press </ORGANIZATION> in an interview. `` The regulations carry out the commitment he made to us.'' <PERSON> Nicholas </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Brady </PERSON> is secretary of the <ORGANIZATION> Treasury </ORGANIZATION>.
