<BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>ATLANTA (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 Angry abortion opponents on Friday urged media magnate <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> to quit calling them `` bozos'' and other names and give their cause equal time on his cable network. About 10 people picketed <PERSON> Turner </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> CNN </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Center </ORGANIZATION> in downtown <LOCATION> Atlanta </LOCATION> to object to <ORGANIZATION> Turner </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Broadcasting </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Systems </ORGANIZATION>' planned cablecast of a documentary, `` Abortion For Survival.'' The show, produced from the point of view of those who favor a woman's right to have an abortion, is scheduled to be shown on <PERSON> Turner </PERSON>'s TBS network next Thursday. The protesters also objected to his labeling anti-abortion forces `` idiots'' and `` bozos'' in a talk with cable operators Wednesday. One carried a sign that read, `` I'm no Bozo.'' The demonstrators demanded that <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> also program an anti-abortion documentary, `` Eclipse of Reason.'' The film, produced by Dr. <PERSON> Bernard </PERSON> <PERSON> Nathanson </PERSON>, shows a fetus aborted at 24 weeks. <ORGANIZATION> TBS </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Kitsie </PERSON> <PERSON> Bassett </PERSON> <PERSON> Riggall </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> TBS </ORGANIZATION> received a letter from the <ORGANIZATION> National </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Right </ORGANIZATION> to Life requesting the use of of `` Eclipse of Reason.'' `` It is under consideration, but no decision has been made,'' she said. Turner announced the program during a meeting of cable executives. He said that after the program, there would be a televised debate including Rep. <PERSON> Robert </PERSON> <PERSON> Dornan </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-Calif </LOCATION>., an abortion foe; <PERSON> Faye </PERSON> <PERSON> Wattleton </PERSON> of Planned Parenthood; and <PERSON> Nellie </PERSON> <PERSON> Gray </PERSON>, president of March for Life `` We'll give the other bozos a chance to talk back,'' <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> said. `` They look like idiots anyway.'' <ORGANIZATION> Georgia </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Right </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> to </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Life </ORGANIZATION> spokeswoman <PERSON> Mary </PERSON> <PERSON> Boyert </PERSON> said in a statement Friday that the group thinks <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> has failed in his responsibility to be impartial. They also objected to the flippant nature of his comments. `` Abortion is no joke. Babies are dying. It does n't take much brains to know that,'' the statement said. `` <PERSON> Ted </PERSON> <PERSON> Turner </PERSON> has thrown down the gauntlet, and we intend to fight.'' Ms. <PERSON> Boyert </PERSON> said her group does n't plan continued focus on <PERSON> Turner </PERSON>, but wanted him to know they are `` disappointed with the biased programming.'' TBS got about 20 calls from viewers Thursday, about half of them objecting to <PERSON> Turner </PERSON>'s comments or the premise of the abortion program. Spokeswoman <PERSON> Kirsten </PERSON> <PERSON> White </PERSON> said the volume of calls about doubled Friday, but could n't provide exact numbers or say what the callers said.
