ot clear how they gained entry, since the door was not damaged, the police official said. The Kurds are an ethnic minority of 20 million living in <LOCATION> Turkey </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>, and <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> and small enclaves of 500,000 each in <LOCATION> Syria </LOCATION> and the <LOCATION> Soviet </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Union </LOCATION>. Qassemlou, who was educated in <LOCATION> France </LOCATION>, lived there in exile for several years. He fought the Iranian government alongside the <ORGANIZATION> Mujahedeen </ORGANIZATION> and other opposition groups in the early 1980s. However, he later supported negotiations. The Kurdish <ORGANIZATION> Democratic </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Party </ORGANIZATION> has another wing based in <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION>. Under Iranian sponsorship, it is fighting <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> for an independent homeland for Iraqi Kurds. The Iraqi government recently has been accused of forcibly evacuating thousands of Kurds from their homes, razing towns in the northern Kurdish homeland and resettling Kurds in the south of the country. The government says the resettlement is to improve life for the impoverished Kurds. A short time before <LOCATION> Iraq </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Iran </LOCATION> agreed to their cease-fire, the Iraqis dropped poison gas on the Kurdish town of <LOCATION> Halabja </LOCATION>, killing an estimated 4,000 civilians. The Kurds claim thousands more were killed in similar chemical weapons attacks last fall.
