</TEXT>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Stock prices posted their eighth straight gain Thursday as traders waited hopefully for new signs of a slowing economy. The Dow Jones industrials average rose 5.69 to 2,538.32. The dollar moved mostly higher against major foreign currencies. Bond prices were slightly lower as traders awaited the release of economic data today. Soybean futures prices rebounded following news of a legal challenge to an order that traders liquidate holdings in the July contract. Wheat and oat futures advanced; corn futures finished mixed; cattle futures were up sharply; precious metals were mixed.
</TEXT>
