<SECOND>PM-Wall Street 10am,0347</SECOND>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 The stock market edged upward today in a hesitant response to a fresh barrage of statistics on the state of the economy. The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 5.88 to 2,544.20 in the first half hour of trading. Gainers held a narrow lead over losers in the early tally of <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 366 up, 341 down and 517 unchanged. Volume on the <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> came to 27.09 million shares as of 10 a.m. on Wall Street. Several reports from the government this morning lent support to the widespread view that the pace of economic activity was continuing to slow, fulfilling a primary goal of the <ORGANIZATION> Federal </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Reserve </ORGANIZATION>'s credit policy. The <ORGANIZATION> Fed </ORGANIZATION> reported a 0.2 percent drop in industrial production for June, and a decline in capacity utilization at the nation's factories, utilities and mines Separately, the <ORGANIZATION> Labor </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> said its producer price index of finished goods dropped 0.1 percent last month. That number came in below advance estimates calling for an increase of between 0.1 and 0.3 percent. However, the producer price index, excluding its sometimes volatile food and energy components, was up 0.7 percent. That left market participants without an unequivocal signal of slackening inflationary pressures, analysts said. Among actively traded blue chips, <ORGANIZATION> Eastman </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kodak </ORGANIZATION> rose \ to 49 and <ORGANIZATION> General </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Motors </ORGANIZATION> gained -RRB- to 42 -RRB-, but <ORGANIZATION> International </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Business </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Machines </ORGANIZATION> dropped -LRB- to 114 -RCB- and <ORGANIZATION> DuPont </ORGANIZATION> was down \ at 112 \ The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>'s composite index of all its listed common stocks rose .22 to 184.53. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index was up .26 at 367.90. On Wednesday the Dow Jones industrial average rose 5.69 to 2,538.32, extending its gain so far this month to 98.26 points. Advancing issues outnumbered declines by about 7 to 6 on the <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION>, with 789 up, 661 down and 527 unchanged. <ORGANIZATION> Big </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> volume totaled 153.80 million shares, against 160.55 million in the previous session.
