<HEAD>W.R. Grace Reports Lower Second Quarter Results</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> W.R. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Grace </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> reported Friday a 31.5 percent drop in second-quarter earnings, reflecting higher interest expenses. For the three-month period ended June 30, Grace's after-tax income totaled $ 44.07 million, or 52 cents a share, down from $ 64.4 million, or 76 cents a share, in the comparable 1988 period. Revenue of the New York-based specialty chemicals company rose 4.4 percent to $ 1.51 billion from $ 1.45 billion a year earlier. Company Chairman <PERSON> J. </PERSON> <PERSON> Peter </PERSON> <PERSON> Grace </PERSON> attributed the earnings decline partly to higher interest expense and projected an improvement in the second half. `` Despite these lower figures for the quarter, we remain optimistic that full year income will exceed the $ 2.26 per share reported for 1988,'' <PERSON> Grace </PERSON> said. For the first six months of 1989, <ORGANIZATION> Grace </ORGANIZATION>'s profit fell 31.7 percent to $ 73.5 million, or 86 cents a share, from $ 107.52 million, or $ 1.27 a share, in the year-earlier quarter. The company's revenue in the first half totaled $ 2.91 billion, up 6 percent from $ 2.74 billion a year ago.
