<HEAD>Seeks $100 Million For Reorganization Expenses</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By BRIAN MURPHY</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Business Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>MIAMI (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION> on Friday requested to use $ 100 million from a court-monitored escrow account toward its rebuilding program, and union leaders said it was a sign the carrier is struggling in the 4-month-old strike. A spokesman for the Miami-based carrier contends it was well documented that <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> could use some profits from the sale of planes and other assets in its reorganization into a smaller company. Eastern filed papers in <LOCATION> U.S. </LOCATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bankruptcy </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Court </ORGANIZATION> in <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> seeking to free the $ 100 million to pay off expenses. Eastern spokesman <PERSON> Robin </PERSON> <PERSON> Matell </PERSON> said he does not know when a ruling may be issued. `` It was known from the beginning that we could use some of the proceeds from our asset transactions for rebuilding,'' said <PERSON> Matell </PERSON>. `` I do n't see why anyone is shocked by this.'' But the <ORGANIZATION> Air </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Line </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pilots </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Association </ORGANIZATION> on Friday said <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION>'s request for the funds suggests cash-flow problems in operating a smaller carrier `` Eastern's request is evidence that the company's reorganization plan is seriously flawed,'' the <ORGANIZATION> ALPA </ORGANIZATION> statement said. <PERSON> Matell </PERSON> said <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> is planning to sell $ 1.8 billion in assets, including a proposed $ 206.5 million sale of 16 planes, two Canadian routes and 13 gates at <LOCATION> Philadelphia </LOCATION> <LOCATION> International </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Airport </LOCATION> to <ORGANIZATION> Midway </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Airlines </ORGANIZATION>. In June, <ORGANIZATION> Eastern </ORGANIZATION> sold its profitable Northeast shuttle se